ration of how these changes are restructuring the social division of labor and its geographies as well as the stratifications and lines of struggle.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAssembly-line methods. 0aHigh technology industriesxEmployees. 0aIndustrial managementxTechnological innovations. 0aInternet industry -- Employees. 0aInternet industryxEmployees. 0aTechnological innovationsxEconomic aspects. 0aTechnological innovationsxSocial aspects. 0aUnskilled labor. 7aTechnology & Engineering / General.2bisacsh  aLabor, factory, automation, platforms, migration, infrastructure, digital capitalism, digital Taylorism, gig economy, class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099422308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2022z9783110994193oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226815503423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226815503/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099422-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEIb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022